    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-09-29</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-10-25T17:10:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Hospital Payment Improvement and Equity Act of 2006 - Directs the Secretary of Health and Human Services to establish a process under which a hospital may appeal its wage index classification under title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act and select another area within the state (or, at the Secretary's discretion, within a contiguous state) to which to be reclassified.</p> <p>Prescribes special rules for: (1) a competitively disadvantaged hospital in a single-hospital Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA) surrounded by rural counties; and (2) rehabilitation hospitals and rehabilitation units.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
